output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of all subjects, 5 years after graduation, the industry with the highest proportion of female graduates is Transportation and storage, and the median earnings of females in this industry were £24,800. The industry with the highest proportion of male graduates was Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply and the median earnings of males in this industry were £25,700.

The biggest difference in proportions is seen in Transportation and storage where the proportion of female graduates is 9.5 percentage points higher than the proportion of male graduates. The biggest difference in median earnings is seen in Financial and insurance activities where the median earnings of female graduates were £4,300 higher than the median earnings of male graduates.The group with the highest earnings was female graduates in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of £27,900).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of all subjects by sex, five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
